text: Julia du Plessis (born 27 May 1996) is a South African high jumper. A child prodigy, her personal best jump is 1.88 metres, achieved in March 2012 in Germiston. In the age-specific categories she went on to win the bronze medal at the 2013 World Youth Championships, the silver medal at the 2015 African Junior Championships and finished twelfth at the 2012 World Junior Championships. She won the bronze medal at the 2015 African Games, finished eighth at the 2016 African Championships, tenth at the 2017 Summer Universiade and sixth at the 2018 African Championships. ==References== Category:1996 births Category:Living people Category:South African female high jumpers Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2015 African Games Category:African Games bronze medalists for South Africa Category:African Games medalists in athletics (track and field) Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2019 African Games Category:Competitors at the 2017 Summer Universiade
